00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:15.530
Hey yall I want to show you how to spice up
those red lips with a little bit of gold just

00:00:15.530 --> 00:00:17.280
in time for Valentine's Day.

00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:22.560
So before we get started, no I am not trying
to get into make-up because that is simply

00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:27.890
not my thing, but I do like to dress up my
lips for special occasions so the first thing

00:00:27.890 --> 00:00:31.500
I'm doing is putting on this lip smacker lip
gloss because I like it!

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:35.920
I mean it tastes great and it keeps my lips
moisturized.

00:00:35.920 --> 00:00:42.780
Now I'm just going to take this lip pencil
which is the color cherry, obviously by MAC,

00:00:42.780 --> 00:00:55.229
and line just the outer part of my lips.

00:00:55.229 --> 00:01:01.050
Now I'm just going to take this MAC lipstick
which is the color frost bronze shimmer or

00:01:01.050 --> 00:01:09.770
something like that, and fill in the middle
of my lips.

00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:13.620
So this right here shows you how much I am
not into make-up because I don't even have

00:01:13.620 --> 00:01:20.320
any lip brushes so I'm using my ring finger
to blend out that red and gold so the line

00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:27.350
isn't so harsh between it.

00:01:27.350 --> 00:01:30.259
Now I'm just adding extra...uh-oh.

00:01:30.259 --> 00:01:32.119
I have lipstick on my teeth.

00:01:32.119 --> 00:01:37.130
So a trick that my mom taught me was to stick
your finger in your mouth and do just like

00:01:37.130 --> 00:01:39.020
that...

00:01:39.020 --> 00:01:45.610
Anyway I'm adding more gold just to the middle
of my lips to give it a more ombre and shimmery

00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:46.610
effect.

00:01:46.610 --> 00:01:52.159
And that is it yall if your mom taught you
that get lipstick off your teeth trick tell

00:01:52.159 --> 00:01:53.789
me down in the comment section.

